column26:
The UAP Make build target short-circuits incorrectly due to already being up to date when UAP is built using Make on a Windows machine.

*Reproduction Steps:*

# Set up UAP project on a Windows machine
# Build the UAP application using Make ({{make}} or {{make uap}} in the terminal)

*Current Outcome:*

UAP Make target skips running due to already being ‘up to date’.

*Desired Outcome:*

UAP Make target runs unless the UAP executable and all of the UAP codebase are up to date.
column94: 10/Jul/24 3:10 PM;712020:d67b4b8a-9508-4ea0-b812-b399a2d24976;May be caused by lack of {{uap}} target prerequisites. Will start investigation on this front.
column95: 11/Jul/24 11:37 AM;712020:d67b4b8a-9508-4ea0-b812-b399a2d24976;Was actually caused by Windows make requiring target to be filenames; added UAP file prerequisites anyways.
